&lt;p&gt;在一般情况下&amp;#xff0c;直接连接到电源地是最优的连接方式&amp;#xff0c;因为电源地提供了一个稳定的参考电平&amp;#xff0c;可以有效地抵消干扰信号。当然&amp;#xff0c;这并不意味着只有直接连接才能达到最好的抗干扰效果。实际上&amp;#xff0c;一些特殊的情况下&amp;#xff0c;其他连接方式也可能达到更好的效果。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;对于模拟电路和数字电路&amp;#xff0c;它们的信号特性和抗干扰能力有很大的差异。模拟电路信号具有连续性和无限变化的特性&amp;#xff0c;容易受到外界干扰。而数字电路信号只有两种状态&amp;#xff0c;相对抗干扰能力更强。因此&amp;#xff0c;在连接模拟电路和数字电路时&amp;#xff0c;应该采取一些措施来减少干扰。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;对于模拟地和数字地的连接方式&amp;#xff0c;一般来说&amp;#xff0c;它们应该分别连接到电源地&amp;#xff0c;以保证它们之间的干扰互不影响。这种连接方式可以避免数字信号对模拟信号的影响&amp;#xff0c;并且可以最大限度地减少电路的干扰。&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The redundant permutations are filtered out because the start node of each returned permutation is always less than all the remaining elements (under some ordering).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suspect the problem is in a missing implementation of these steps:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;AK:= adjacency structure of strong component K with least vertex in
  subgraph of G induced by {s, s+ 1, n};&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;s := least vertex in V;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These steps should ensure that the start of each permutation (s) is always less than the rest of the permutation but I cannot see code to implement this, instead you seem to loop through every node in the strongly connected component.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

